Preconditions:
- The input array `arr` is not null.
- The length of the input array `arr` is greater than or equal to 1.
- Each element in the input array `arr` is an integer.
- Each element in the input array `arr` is greater than or equal to 1.
- Each element in the input array `arr` is less than or equal to 30000.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer.
- The returned integer is the sum of the minimum values of all contiguous subarrays of the input array `arr`.
- The returned integer is modulo 1000000007.